@endnode

@node "13_0" "History"
@{fg fill}@{u}13. History@{uu}@{fg text}
r1 beta7 (22.08.2013)
* BUG: Fixed a nasty bug, where a (deleted/changed) soft link in the Sys: partition to a folder somewhere, could cause AmiSystemRestore to delete everything inside that folder.  This could easily happen if RunInUAE was installed on Sys:.  Many thanks to Michael Rupp for reporting symptoms of this nasty bug, and testing the fix.
* BUG: The GUI would crash if you attempted to manually delete a restore point which contained a soft link.

r1 beta6 (28.01.2013)
* NEW: Windows can now remember their position & size!  (Remember to snapshot them like any other MUI program.)
* CHG: The main window no-longer briefly opens when the first restore point is created!
* CHG: No-longer reports "recursion avoided" to the debug log.  Thanks to (I think only) Hubert Maier & Tommysammy reporting when it was logged.
* BUG: The destruction of soft links would sometimes incorrectly be interpreted as hard links.  (Bug added by beta5.)
* BUG: Fixed sometimes reporting an error, which was not clearly associated with AmiSystemRestore.  Thanks to Chris Young, Scott Cambell & George Wyche for reporting the problem & trying to help me fix it.  The error message in question is this one:  EXCEPTION: " ERR"; fileSize(); failed to obtain size of file (2).

r1 beta5 (01-12-2012)
* NEW: The length of a restore point name is now REALLY unlimited (I had overlooked restrictions in a couple of places).
* NEW: Added a "Restore blacklist", so when Restoring it automatically unticks files inside blacklisted folders.  This was needed for AmigaOS4.1 Update 6, to prevent users accidentally restoring AmiUpdate's Rollback folder (which is now stored on SYS:).
* NEW: Now able to monitor AmiUpdate when it has been run from the Shell rather than the Workbench.
* CHG: Previous wrongly-stored empty backup files (see next line below) will be fixed by the installer, as they would create problems when restoring.  @{fg shadow}(This will probably only affect a handful of people.)@{fg text}
* BUG: Fixed a bogus empty backup file being stored, when a file was created using a multi-assignment path that already existed but only in one of the later assignments. (phew!)
* BUG: Fixed empty restore points showing as 1KB in size. (Bug added by beta2.)
* BUG: Fixed "Installer avoids creating empty restore points" not working. (Bug added by beta2.)
* BUG: Fixed certain cases where writing to the debug log would hang the whole OS, although no-one reported such problems. (Bug added by beta4.)

r1 beta4 (20-09-2012)
* NEW: Got rid of the mostly-harmless "getCurrentRestorePoint_handle()" debug log entries, thanks to feedback from a few people (inc. Scott Cambell).
* NEW: The window now resizes itself when the "Show size of restore point" preferences is changed.
* NEW: AISS is no-longer required for the toolbar to have images (and the installer correctly handles AISS not being available).  Thanks to bug report by Tony Wyatt.
* CHG: Changed how some stuff writes to the debug log; provides more info, and won't fail to be written when two things try to write to it simultaneously.
* CHG: The installer now better handles installation problems.

r1 beta3 (09-09-2012)
* BUG: Fixed the Restoring window showing many bogus folders.  (This was harmless, but made it hard to use.)
* BUG: Hopefully stopped the installer crashing when the user has disabled OS4.1's new WBStartup in favour of the old SYS:WBStartup.  Thanks to Dragster for the bug report.  (This also means it should install correctly on OS4.0.)

r1 beta2 (04-09-2012)
* NEW: When iconified it now uses it's own icon (rather than MUI's default icon).
* NEW: The length of a restore point name is now unlimited (previously it was limited to about 50 characters).
* NEW: Now has some proper icons thanks to Frank 'cha05e90' Ruthe (which were based upon icons by Martin 'mason' Merz).
       Installer & AmigaGuide icons by Martin 'mason' Merz (which TommySammy sent to me).
* NEW: Now uses a requester instead of Ringhio to report at start-up that the debug log is not empty.
* NEW: The documentation now mentions AmiUpdate's RollBack feature.
* CHG: Finally understood the recursive Write() problem, and prevented it from happening in the first place (rather than just working-around the problem after it happened).  I am now much happier about AmiSystemRestore's likely reliability.
* CHG: When the user creates a restore point, it now rejects an empty name.
* BUG: Fixed installation failing for multi-language installers with a shared script.  Thanks to Unimon for the bug report.
* BUG: Fixed window being tiny & in the top-left corner of the screen, if the program was started iconified & a restore point was created before the window was ever opened.
* BUG: Simultaneous attempts to modify Sys: would often cause the state file to be regenerated, which was entirely unnecessary.
* BUG: Fixed new name of restore point not being shown, when the name was merely truncated & the restore point sizes were being shown.

r1 beta1 (30-07-2012)
* NEW: First public beta release :-)

* NEW: Folders are shown for Restoring, and clicking on them (de)selects everything inside that folder.
* NEW: Limited Restore mode now shows files from unticked restore points, thus allowing you to tick those files.  Makes this mode much more useful!
* NEW: Now responds to quit requests from Exchange!  Thanks to prodding from Chris Young.
* NEW: Running it a second time now causes the first one to open, rather than complaining.
* NEW: Renaming multiple items now halts renaming when cancelled, and also unticks items that have been renamed.
* NEW: At start-up now detects & handles the current or previous restore points being missing.
* NEW: Now reports if the "FakeInstaller" is somehow missing.  And now looks for it in PROGDIR: instead of the current dir. 
* NEW: Now reports at start-up if the debug log is not empty.
* NEW: The main window now retains it's size & position when it refreshes (due to a new restore point, etc).
* CHG: Restore points below 512 bytes now show as being 1 KB instead of 0 KB (unless really empty).

* BUG: Fixed files not being protected after the SYS: partition was relabelled.
* BUG: In rare cases a file would not be protected (due to a race-like condition).
* BUG: Fixed a possibly-harmless error being reported in the debug log (due to a race condition).

r1 beta (18-01-2012)
* The last (private) beta release.  No stability problems noticed after this...

r1 beta (06-09-2011)
* The first (private) beta release.

r1 alpha (29-06-2011)
* The first (private) alpha release. 
@endnode
